HEADWORD: Dispiritment
<hw>Dis*pir"it*ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Depression of
spirits; discouragement.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Procter, in evident distress and <qex>dispiritment</qex>, was
waiting the slow conclusion of this.</q>
<rj><qau>Carlyle.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dispiteous</ent>⟦br⟧
